  "body": "with hardhat-ganache happily installed and added to my hardhat.config.ts file, it looks like the hardhat NetworkUserConfig object doesn't know to expect the dbPath object. Has anyone run into something similar or gotten this flag working? \r\n\r\n**hardhat.config.ts**\r\n\r\n```import \"@typechain/hardhat\"\r\nimport \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\"\r\nimport \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-waffle\"\r\nimport {HardhatUserConfig} from \"hardhat/types\"\r\nimport \"tsconfig-paths/register\"\r\nimport \"hardhat-contract-sizer\"\r\nimport \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ganache\";\r\n\r\nimport emulate from \"./scripts/emulate\";\r\nimport {task} from \"hardhat/internal/core/config/config-env\";\r\n\r\nconst config: HardhatUserConfig = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.8\",\r\n  defaultNetwork: \"ganache\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    localhost: {\r\n      allowUnlimitedContractSize: true,\r\n    },\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      allowUnlimitedContractSize: true,\r\n      chainId: 31337,\r\n    },\r\n    ganache: {\r\n      url: \"https://localhost:8089\",\r\n      dbPath: \"db/\"\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  mocha: {\r\n    timeout: 150000\r\n  }\r\n}\r\nexport default config```\r\n",
